    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it doesn't feel temporary. it feels final. everything that made me \"me\" was my work and my status. now that they're stripped away, there's just this empty shell. how do you even rebuild when the foundation is completely turned to ash? it feels like the person i was is actually dead.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's a heavy realization, but the \"you\" that was built on external things was always just a facade, a performance. The ash is the clearing, not the end; it's the space where something quieter, more authentic, can finally take root. You don't have to rebuild the old structure; you can choose to build something entirely new, one small, honest thing at a time.",
      "source": "target",
